Configuration File Parser
README Summary
Purpose
Reads a block of key=value configuration text and prints each entry with a capitalized label. Built with Gos standard library — no external packages needed.

Language & Packages
• Language: Go (Golang) 1.18+
• Packages: fmt, strings
• No external dependencies

 Input /  Output
Input
Output
host=localhost
Host: localhost
port=8080
Port: 8080
debug=true
Debug: true


 Code
package main
import ( "fmt"  "strings" )
func main() {
    config := "host=localhost\nport=8080\ndebug=true"
    for _, line := range strings.Split(config, "\n") {
        parts := strings.SplitN(line, "=", 2)
        key := strings.ToUpper(parts[0][:1]) + parts[0][1:]
        fmt.Println(key + ": " + parts[1])
    }
}

 How It Works
• strings.Split breaks the config into individual lines on each \n
• strings.SplitN splits each line on = into a key and value (max 2 parts)
• parts[0][:1] takes the first letter of the key and ToUpper capitalizes it
• parts[0][1:] keeps the rest of the key unchanged
• Println joins and prints the capitalized key, colon, and value

 How to Run
• Save the file as main.go
go run main.go

— End of README —
